"{\n    \"Title\": \"oe eee Lakehead University\",\n    \"row 1\": \"Notes to Financial Statements\",\n    \"row 2\": \"April 30, 2018 (in thousands of dollars)\",\n    \"row 3\": \"2. Summary of Significant Accounting Policies (continued)\",\n    \"row 4\": \"h. Employee Future Benefits\",\n    \"row 5\": \"The University accrues its obligations under the defined benefit plans as the employees render\",\n    \"row 6\": \"the services necessary to earn the pension and other retirement benefits.\",\n    \"row 7\": \"The University accounts for the defined benefit component of the Pension Plan for Professional\",\n    \"row 8\": \"Staff using the immediate recognition approach. The University recognizes the amount of the\",\n    \"row 9\": \"accrued benefit obligation, net of the fair value of the plan assets measured at year-end,\",\n    \"row 10\": \"adjusted for any valuation allowance, in the balance sheets. Actuarial gains and losses are\",\n    \"row 11\": \"included in the cost of the plans for the year. The accrued benefit obligation for the pension\",\n    \"row 12\": \" plan is determined based on an actuarial valuation using funding assumptions. The most recent\",\n    \"row 13\": \"actuarial valuation of the pension plan for funding purposes has been conducted as of December\",\n    \"row 14\": \"31, 2015, and the next required valuation will be as of December 31, 2018. In years where an\",\n    \"row 15\": \"actuarial valuation is not prepared, the University uses a roll-forward technique to estimate the\",\n    \"row 16\": \"accrued liability using assumptions from the most recent actuarial valuation report.\",\n    \"row 17\": \"3. Accounts Receivable \",\n    \"row 18\": \"~ Accounts receivable consists of the following:\",\n    \"row 19\": \" 2018 2017\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Tuition and residence fees $ 2,053 \\u00a7$ 2,304\",\n    \"row 21\": \"Interest and sundry accounts 7,793 5,026\",\n    \"row 22\": \"Sponsored research monies 2,484 3,786\",\n   